entary processes"''; Professor of Chemistry; Principal Investigator, Materials and Molecular Research Division, [[Lawrence Berkeley Laboratory]]; *'''[[Willard Libby]]''', B.S. 1931, Ph.D. 1933 â Professor of Chemistry, Nobel laureate (1960, Chemistry),<ref>{{Cite document|url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/1960/libby-bio.html|title= Nobel Lectures, Chemistry 1942â1962| publisher=Elsevier Publishing Company|location=[[Amsterdam]]|year=1964|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref> ''"for his method to use [[carbon-14]] for age determination in [[archaeology]], [[geology]], [[geophysics]], and other branches of science"'' *[[John C. Mather]], Ph.D. 1974 â Nobel laureate (2006, Physics),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9436258/John-C-Mather|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20071206034236/http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9436258/John-C-Mather|archivedate=2007-12-06|title=John C. Mather|publisher=[[EncyclopÃ¦dia Britannica]]|accessdate=2007-04-16}}</ref> for the ''"discovery of the [[blackbody]] form and [[anisotropy]] of the [[cosmic microwave background radiation]]"'' *[[Mario Molina]], Ph.D. 1972â Nobel laureate (1995, Chemistry),<ref>{{Cite document|url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/1995/molina-autobio.html|title= Les Prix Nobel. The Nobel Prizes 1995|author=Tore FrÃ¤ngsmyr, editor| publisher=Nobel Foundation|location=Stockholm|year=1996|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref> for ''"work in atmospheric chemistry, particularly concerning the formation and decomposition of [[ozone]]"'' *[[Kary Mullis]], Ph.D. 1973 â Nobel laureate (1993, Chemistry),<ref>{{Cite document|url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/1993/mullis-autobio.html|title= Les Prix Nobel. The Nobel Prizes 1993|author=Tore FrÃ¤ngsmyr, editor| publisher=Nobel Foundation|location=Stockholm|year=1994|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref> ''"for his invention of the [[polymerase chain reaction]] (PCR) method"'' *[[Douglass