ze.org/nobel_prizes/economics/laureates/2005/schelling-autobio.html|title= Les Prix Nobel. The Nobel Prizes 2005|author=Karl Grandin, editor| publisher=Nobel Foundation|location=Stockholm|year=2006|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref> ''"for having enhanced our understanding of conflict and cooperation through [[game theory|game-theory]] analysis"'' *'''[[Glenn T. Seaborg]]''', Ph.D. 1937 â University Professor of Chemistry; Associate Director, [[Lawrence Berkeley Laboratory]]; Chancellor, Berkeley campus (1958â1961); Nobel laureate (1951, Chemistry), <ref>{{Cite document|url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/economics/laureates/2005/schelling-autobio.html|title= Nobel Lectures, Chemistry 1942â1962|publisher=Elsevier Publishing Company|location=[[Amsterdam]]|year=1964|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref> for ''"discoveries in the chemistry of the [[transuranium]] elements"'' *[[Hamilton O. Smith]], B.A. 1952 â Nobel laureate (1978, Physiology or Medicine),<ref>{{Cite document|url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/economics/laureates/2005/schelling-autobio.html|title=Les Prix Nobel. The Nobel Prizes 1978|author=Wilhelm Odelberg, editor|publisher=Nobel Foundation|location=Stockholm|year=1979|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref> ''"for the discovery of [[restriction enzymes]] and their application to problems of molecular genetics"'' *'''[[Otto Stern]]''', L.L.D 1930 â Nobel laureate (1943, Nobel Prize in Physics),<ref>{{Cite document|url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1943/stern-bio.html|title=Nobel Lectures, Physics 1942â1962|publisher= Elsevier Publishing Company|location=[[Amsterdam]]|year=1964|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref> ''"for his contribution to the development of the molecular ray method and his discovery of the [[magnetic moment]] of the [[proton]]"'' *[[Henry Taube]], Ph.D. 1940 â Nobel laureate (1983, Chemistry ),<ref>{{Cite document|url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/1983/taube-cv.html|title= Les Prix Nobel. Th